      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Grignard reagents (alkylmagnesium halides) undergo a general and very useful reaction with ketones. Methylmagnesium bromide, for example, reacts with cyclohexanone to yield a product with the formula C<sub>7</sub>H<sub>14</sub>O. What is the structure of this product if it has an IR absorption at 3400 cm<sup>–1</sup>?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaVFVIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--6087ab935759eae8c588800e34d2dd6ec7433913/OChem_12_EC_012.jpg\" alt=\"Cyclohexanone reacts first with methyl magnesium bromide and then hydronium ion to form an unknown product represented by a question mark.\">",
